review_blob: Poured pitch black. Sweet malty aroma. Very sweet. Roast malt and caramel taste with notes of oak and vanilla. A bit boozy, but very well done.
Poured very dark, little head. Aroma of smokey roast malt. Taste is dominated by roasted malt with dark fruit and a touch of smoke. Hint of bitterness. Very nice effort.
Poured black with a tan head. Roast malt and coffee aroma. Subtle flavors. Toasted malt, bread, some caramel, maybe a touch of hops.

Poured muddy brown with a tan head. Sweet spicy aroma. The taste was quite sweet, almost too sweet. Lots of caramel and raisins, some spices like nutmeg and clove. Nice oaky accent to it. Very nice, but hard to swallow the $10 a bottle price tag.

Poured golden with a medium white head. Light hoppy aroma. Taste has a nice malt base with floral hops present. Some bitterness. In general clean and easy drinking. Light beer with a little extra taste and bitterness. Solid summer session beer.

On tap at the brewhouse. Pitch black with a small tan head. Aroma of mainly roast malt. Taste was chocolately and malty and fairly sweet. Very thick and creamy. Satisfying. One of the better stouts I have come across.
Poured reddish brown with a tan head. Yeast and fruit aroma. Taste was malty with some spice, caramel and a touch of cocoa. Some dark fruit as well. Very nice.
Poured yellow with a thin white head. Lightly hopped aroma. Taste is grassy hops and a touch of roast malt. Hint of grapefruit. Slightly bitter.
Poured pale yellow. Light citrus aroma. Taste was lemony, lightly spiced with some citrus and yeast. Nice light summer beer.
Poured pitch black with a tan head. Coffee and malt aroma. Taste was coffee, malt and oatmeal with a hint of chocolate and some bitterness.
Poured cloudy yellow. Light fruity and buttery aroma. Flavor was mainly butterscotch and fruity with some yeast. A touch sweet.
Poured oily black with a tan head. The aroma was mainly coffee. Taste was sweet and malty with some coffee and chocolate notes.
Poured amber with a thin tan head. Sweet malty aroma. Big burst of vanilla up front. Like a vanilla shake. Some malt and caramel and nutty, but mainly its about the vanillla sweetness. Not too bad.
Poured cloudy yellow. Light fruity aroma. Light flavor with touches of malt and floral hops. Very subtle. Drinkable summer beer, but nothing stands out.
2008 Release. Poured cloudy brown. Thin head. Pine and grapefruit aroma. Very thick and sweet with soem malt and caramel notes. Hoppy bitterness as it warms.
Poured golden in color. Aroma was light floral hops. Taste was floral hops, malt and some fruitiness. Not bad.
Poured golden with a thin white head. Yeast and malt aroma. Banana, yeast and citrus taste with a touch of butter and a dry finish. Overall not too bad.
Poured pitch black with a brown head. Raisin and dark fruit aroma. Very sweet. Creamy chocolate, roast malt and dark fruit. Rich and complex. Maybe a bit too sweet, but I love sweets.
Poured cloudy copper. Caramel and malt aroma. Creamy, buttery mouthfeel. Taste of buterscotch, caramel , fruit and earthy hops. Ver ynice.
Poured cloudy copper. Floral hop and grapefruit aroma. Smooth palate. Not all that biter. Taste of grapefruit and grassy, earthy hops.
Poured cloudy yellow. Sweet malt aroma. Taste was quite sweet, malty and buttery.
Poured dark brown with a big tan head. Aroma of dark bread and yeast. Taste is lightly spiced and bready with some clove and a hint of smoke.
Poured pitch black. Malty, coffee aroma. Taste was mainly roast malt, coffee and cocoa. More bitter than I expected. Not too bad.

Poured pale yellow with a white head. Pine hops and grapefruit aroma. Alcohol burn right up front, but it mellows as you go along. Sweet to start with some grapefruit and malt and the bitterness becomes more apparent as it warms. I am not usually a big fan of IPAs, but this one is very good.
Poured black with a tan head. Aroma of roast malt and dark chocolate. Taste was toasted malt, chocolate and a hint of cherry. Just as promised. Creamy texture. Very satisfying.
beer_name: Tyranena BGW Paradise by the Dashboard Lights

review_blob: Poured cloudy yellow with a foamy white head. Yeast and clove aroma. Very bold taste - yeasty, clove, banana and lemony citrus. A touch dry as well. Another solid beer by New Glarus. They make this one year round, so it will tide me over until I can get some Dancing Man Wheat later this summer.
Poured very dark brown. Aroma of roast malt and cocoa. Taste was much the same, roast malt and cocoa with a touch of bitterness. A bit thin, but very drinkable.
Poured golden in color. Light honey aroma. Taste was nutty, soapy and sour. Not good at all.

Poured golden with a small head. Aroma of yeast and citrus. The taste had a strong medicinal quality and was not to my liking. It was so prominent that I couldnt get past it and it ended up as a drain pour.
Poured cloudy rust brown. Aroma was sweet with some fruit and floral hops. Taste was fruity with a touch of sourness, something like green apples. Some malt and caramel.
Poured cloudy copper. Aroma of malt, caramel and pine hops. Started off bitter and became quite bitter as it warmed. Some malt, caramel and earthy hops. A bit too bitter for me.
Poured copper in color. Malt and caramel aroma. Taste was sugary sweet with malt, caramel and earthy hops.
Poured amber in color. Grainy aroma. Very thin. Lightly hopped with notes of roast malt and caramel. Not much there.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Poured amber in color. Grainy aroma. Taste was grain, roast malt and herbal tea. Not really to my liking.
Poured amber with a thin head. Roast malt and caramel aroma. Taste was nutty with grassy hops and toasted malt. Maybe a bit thin.
From a bottle at Old Chicago in Eden Prairie, MN. Poured dark with a tan head. Not much aroma. Taste had some vague notes of malt and cocoa. Very smooth but bland.
Poured golden in color. Light malt and fruit aroma. Taste was quite sweet up front with some malt and citrus. Bitterness became apparent as it warmed.
Poured golden with a thin head. Floral hop aroma. Light and crisp with some floral, grassy hops and a touch of malt. Reminds me a little bit of a kolsch. Well done.
Poured cloudy dark brown. Earthy malt aroma. Taste was quite sweet. Some dark fruit and spice. Very creamy mouthfeel.
On tap at Mad Cappers in Stillwater, MN. Looked to be reddish brown in the low light. Lightly spicey aroma. Taste of Belgian yeast, clove and spice. Bready finish. Went well with a meal. Nicely done.

On tap at Old Chicago in Roseville, MN. Cloudy golden with a fairly thick head. Aroma of light spice and yeast. Taste was subtle. Lightly spiced with some clove and yeast. Drinks much life a hefeweizen, but for the touch of dryness.
beer_name: Lift Bridge Farm Girl Belgian Saison

review_blob: Poured deep amber with a thin tan head. Malty aroma. Taste was sweet with notes of roast malt, caramel and cocoa. Maybe a bit thin, but overall not too bad. A nice surprise.
Poured cloudy brown with a thin tan head. Aroma of yeast and clove. Taste of banana, clove and yeast with a hint of sweet malt and caramel. Not too shabby for the price.

Poured copper color with a light tan head. Aroma of grassy hops. Some sweet caramel notes up front, but those quickly disappear. Earthy hops with a hint of spice and a pronounced bitterness as it warms.
Poured pitch black with a big foamy borwn head. Smoke and cocoa aroma. Big smokey malt taste. Dark chocolate accent. Bitterness becomes apparent halfway through the glass.
beer_name: Left Hand SmokeJumper Imperial Smoked Porter

review_blob: Poured copper color. Hoppy aroma with pine and grapefruit. Alcohol bite right up front. Taste of caramel, earthy hops and grapefruit. Quite bitter. Not what I expected from the name or type, but still a decent beer.
Poured reddish brown. Aroma of fruit and sour cherry. Taste was tart and vinegary. Light malt and some sourness. Not to my taste.
beer_name: Flat Earth Rode Haring Flanders Red Ale

review_blob: Pours pitch black. Light cocoa aroma. Roast malt and sweet chocolate flavor, but also noticeable hop bitterness for balance. Creamy mouthfeel as one would expect. Decent stout.
On tap at Applebees in Bloomington, MN. Light citrus aroma. Taste was spicey and lemony citrus with a hint of yeast. Pleasant. Went well with the meal.
Poured pitch black. Sweet malt aroma. Taste was a nice mix of sweet malt, dark fruit and licorice. Reminds me more of a Belgian double or quad.
